<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,582,1147]" pageId="19" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,726,751]" pageId="19" pageNumber="48">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body size 
<quantity box="[597,738,726,751]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="5.35" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="5.2">5.2–5.5 mm</quantity>
. Clypeus appearing dark brown in median third, with lateral thirds distinctly paler (
<figureCitation box="[420,515,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,493,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,493,1914]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5. Heads of Helochares (Hydrobaticus) spp. (A) H. maculicollis (Pennsylvania), (B) H. normatus (California), (C) H. normatus (Arizona), (D) H. nexus n. sp., (E) H. zamora n. sp., (F) H. trujillo n. sp., (G) H. championi, (H) H. sp. A., (I) H. politus n. sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3766300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3766300/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="48">Fig. 5H</figureCitation>
). Pronotum darkened on elytral disc (
<figureCitation box="[967,1060,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,265,1900]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dorsal habitus images of Helochares (Hydrobaticus) spp. (A) H. trujillo n. sp., (B) H. championi Sharp, (C) H. nexus n. sp., (D) H. zamora n. sp., (E) H. sp. A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3766294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3766294/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="48">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Elytra with ten rows of serial punctures, usually appearing weakly impressed into striae. Abdominal ventrites uniformly dark brown; pubescence dense and evenly distributed, the longest hairs shorter than those on the metaventrite. Aedeagus unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
